!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

mug /mʌɡ/

(mugging,mugged,mugs) 

1. N-COUNT A mug is a large, deep cup with straight sides and a handle, used for hot drinks. 圆筒形有柄大杯 

例： He spooned instant coffee into two of the mugs. 他用勺子把速溶咖啡舀进其中两个大杯里。 

2. N-COUNT You can use mug to refer to the mug and its contents, or to the contents only. 一大杯; 一大杯... 

例： He had been drinking mugs of coffee to keep himself awake. 他一直在喝大杯大杯的咖啡让自己保持清醒。 

3. N-COUNT Someone's mug is their face. 脸 [非正式] 

例： He managed to get his ugly mug on TV. 他设法让他那张丑脸上了电视。 

4. V-T If someone mugs you, they attack you in order to steal your money. 袭击并抢劫 

例： I was walking out to my car when this guy tried to mug me. 这家伙企图抢劫我的时候，我正向我的汽车走去。 

5. mugging N-VAR 行凶抢劫 

例： Bank robberies, burglaries, and muggings are reported almost daily in the press. 银行抢劫、入室盗窃以及行凶抢劫几乎在每天的新闻中都有报道。

</div>

